This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories as it discusses the convergence rate and final performance of deep learning models. It also explores the use of heuristics such as learning rate schedules and knowledge distillation, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
